03, 2006.","meanings":["Often used as a feminine equivalent of   Mark  , but in fact a feminine form of <i>Marcius</i>, itself a derivative of   Marcus .  One  St Marcia  is commemorated in a group with Felix, Luciolus, Fortunatus, and others; another with Zenais, Cyria, and Valeria; and a third with Ariston, Crescentian, Eutychian, Urban, Vitalis, Justus, Felicissimus, Felix, and Symphorosa. None is individually very famous."],"variants":[{"name":"Marsha","meanings":["Phonetic spelling of   Marcia  , associated particularly with the American film star  Marsha Hunt  (  b. 1917 )."]}]},{"name":"Gutierrez","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Spanish Jose, Juan, Luis, Jesus, Manuel, Carlos, Francisco, Jorge, Pedro, Raul, Miguel, Roberto.","Spanish (<b>Gutiérrez</b>): patronymic from the medieval personal name <i>Gutierre</i>, from a Visigothic personal name of uncertain form and meaning, perhaps a compound of the elements <i>gunthi</i> ‘battle’ + <i>hairus</i> ‘sword’."],"variants":[{"name":"Gutierez","meanings":["(1997: 130;2007: 1129; 2010: NA)","Some characteristic forenames:  Spanish Jesus, Jose, Ignacio, Manuel, Adalberto, Ana Maria, Angel, Carlota, Emilio, Exiquio, Felipe, Fermin.","Hispanic (<b>Gutiérez</b>): altered form of Spanish <b>Gutiérrez</b> (see   Gutierrez  )."]},{"name":"Gutirrez","meanings":["(2007: 670; 2010: NA)","Hispanic: altered form of Spanish <b>Gutiérrez</b> (see   Gutierrez  )."]},{"name":"Guterrez","meanings":["Hispanic: altered form of Spanish <b>Gutiérrez</b> (see   Gutierrez  )."]},{"name":"Guiterrez","meanings":["(1997: 425;2007: 2304; 2010: NA)","Some characteristic forenames:  Spanish Jose, Juan, Luis, Arturo, Francisco, Alfredo, Jesus, Rafael, Raul, Carlos, Guadalupe, Jose Luis.","Hispanic (<b>Guitérrez</b>): altered form of Spanish <b>Gutiérrez</b> (see   Gutierrez  )."]},{"name":"Gutierres","meanings":["Some characteristic forenam